title: Grateful Dead Live at Buffalo Memorial Auditorium on 1977-05-09
lineage: MAC>R>D>CD source cdr mastering by Jack Warner
description:
Set 1

Help On The Way-> Slipknot!-> Franklin's Tower, Cassidy, Brown Eyed Women, Mexicali Blues, Tennessee Jed, Big River, Peggy-O, Sunrise, The Music Never Stopped

Set 2

Bertha, Good Lovin', Ship of Fools, Estimated Prophet-> The Other One-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Comes A Time-> Sugar Magnolia, E: Uncle John's Band

reviews.review_text: Awesome show great matrix This matrix sounds wonderful. A great opening of help/slipknot/Franklin's. Sonfar I have listened through Tennessee Jed and am looking forward to the rest. Just wish I could have seen them back then. Unfortunately I was only 6 when Jerry died.

Thanks to Everyone that made this possible! At first I was  listening like another Dead show from 77 but was thinking wait. I heard a story about this show but I've never heard this show. I was busy doing other stuff but noticed a really good version of. Peggy-o but OMG the "The Music Never Stopped" on here is fantastic. After it was over I had to listen to it again.
